---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '@/components/Navbar';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Website Showcases - Web Interfaces">
  <Navbar client:idle />
  
  <main class="lg:ml-64 min-h-screen bg-white">
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 pt-20 lg:pt-16 pb-12 lg:pb-16 border-b border-gray-200">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center text-gray-600 hover:text-black transition-colors mb-6">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
          </svg>
          Back
        </a>
        <h1 class="main-text gradient-text mb-4">
          Website Showcases
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg lg:text-xl text-gray-600">
          A curated collection of exceptional web design examples and what makes them effective.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 py-12 lg:py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold text-black mb-6">Learning from Excellence</h2>
        <p class="text-base lg:text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Great web design doesn't happen in a vacuum. By studying exceptional websites, we can identify patterns, 
          techniques, and principles that make interfaces effective, beautiful, and user-friendly.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base lg:text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          This showcase highlights outstanding examples of web design across different industries and styles. 
          Each example is analyzed to reveal what makes it work and how you can apply similar principles.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16">
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Showcase Categories -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 py-12 lg:py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold text-black mb-8">Featured Showcases</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-10">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">1. Minimalist Interfaces</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Exploring websites that embrace simplicity and clarity. These examples demonstrate how less can be more, 
              using white space, typography, and subtle interactions to create elegant experiences.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">2. Interactive Experiences</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Websites that push the boundaries of interactivity. From scroll-triggered animations to immersive 
              storytelling, these examples show how motion and interaction can enhance engagement.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">3. Editorial Design</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Publication and content-focused sites that excel at typography, layout, and readability. 
              These examples demonstrate how to make long-form content engaging and accessible.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">4. E-commerce Excellence</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Online stores that balance aesthetics with conversion optimization. Learn how top e-commerce sites 
              create trust, showcase products, and streamline the purchasing process.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">5. Portfolio & Personal Brands</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Creative portfolios that effectively showcase work and personality. These examples highlight how to 
              create memorable personal brands through thoughtful design and unique presentations.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">6. Product Landing Pages</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Focused pages designed to convert visitors. Study how successful product pages use hierarchy, 
              social proof, and clear calls-to-action to drive desired outcomes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16">
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Analysis Framework -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 py-12 lg:py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold text-black mb-8">How to Analyze</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">First Impressions</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              What stands out immediately? How does the design establish hierarchy and guide your attention?
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">User Flow</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              How easy is it to accomplish key tasks? What friction points exist, and how might they be improved?
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">Visual Language</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              What makes the aesthetic work? Consider typography, color, spacing, and overall style coherence.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">Technical Implementation</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              How is it built? Look at performance, responsiveness, and technical choices that support the design.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Main text - responsive sizing */
  .main-text {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 28px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .main-text {
      font-size: 42px;
      line-height: 44px;
    }
  }

  /* Gradient text - more subtle */
  .gradient-text {
    background: linear-gradient(to right, #6b7280, #374151, #1f2937);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }
</style>

